        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test conditions acceptance criteria",
        "description": "ASTM F1717 specifies a single standardised compression-bending load configuration. Only one test condition (10° offset, 75 mm moment arm) was evaluated; no load-rate or temperature variation was performed. Required: Gradation 3 (multiple conditions spanning COU envelope); achieved: Gradation 2 (single standardised condition, protocol fully documented)."
      },
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under a single ASTM F1717 standardised condition. Gradation 3 would require testing across multiple load rates or environmental conditions; the study design did not include these variations. The shortfall is offset by the multi-laboratory design and the fact that the COU is explicitly scoped to the ASTM F1717 protocol, making additional condition variation outside the intended use envelope."
